Transport bosses are gearing up for a massive influx of spectators to Gleneagles during the Ryder Cup. Ryder Cup influx sparks travel alert Transport bosses are gearing up for a massive influx of spectators to Gleneagles during the Ryder Cup.Around 45,000 golf fans are expected to pour in during the competition days from Friday to Sunday, with around 7500 spectators arriving via the dedicated Ryder Cup trains each day.ScotRail are laying on dedicated early morning and late trains for Ryder Cup ticketholders.But services are already sold out with the operator admitting that services will be too busy to guarantee all passengers a seat.And roads are expected to be nose-to-tail on every day of the event.Fans in Glasgow can watch the tournament, in the fanzone at the city's Merchant Square. 